    <FileReferences>
        <File name=".cursorrules">
            <![CDATA[
# Cursor IDE Notification Rules ğŸ””

## Notification Categories

### System Notifications
- Critical updates
- Security alerts
- Performance warnings
- Environment changes
- Dependency updates

### Development Notifications
- Build status
- Test results
- Linting warnings
- Code coverage reports
- Performance metrics

### Collaboration Notifications
- Pull requests
- Code reviews
- Comments
- Team mentions
- Branch updates

## Notification Settings

### Priority Levels
- HIGH: Immediate notification
  - Security vulnerabilities
  - Build failures
  - Critical system errors
- MEDIUM: Batched notifications
  - Pull request reviews
  - Test results
  - Code quality alerts
- LOW: Daily digest
  - Documentation updates
  - Minor changes
  - General announcements

### Notification Channels
- Desktop notifications
  - Priority: High only
  - Duration: 5 seconds
  - Position: Top right
- In-app notifications
  - All priority levels
  - Customizable filters
  - Interactive responses
- Email notifications
  - Daily summaries
  - Weekly reports
  - Critical alerts only

### Custom Rules
- Project-specific rules
  - Custom notification thresholds
  - Team-based routing
  - Environment-specific alerts
- Team-specific rules
  - Role-based notifications
  - Working hours consideration
  - Priority overrides
- Time-based rules
  - Quiet hours: 22:00-08:00
  - Weekend modifications
  - Holiday schedules

## Configuration

### Desktop Notifications
- Enable sound: false
- Show preview: true
- Auto-dismiss: true
- Focus behavior: bring-to-front
- Click action: open-in-editor

### Email Notifications
- Format: HTML
- Frequency: Daily
- Include attachments: true
- Thread notifications: true
- Reply-to enabled: true

## Best Practices

### Notification Management
1. Configure priority levels appropriately
   - Set clear criteria for each level
   - Regular review of priorities
   - Team alignment on importance
2. Use notification categories effectively
   - Group related notifications
   - Apply consistent filters
   - Maintain clear hierarchy
3. Set up custom rules for specific needs
   - Project requirements
   - Team preferences
   - Individual workflows

### Reducing Noise
1. Filter non-essential notifications
   - Use smart filtering
   - Apply context-aware rules
   - Regular cleanup
2. Group similar notifications
   - Time-based grouping
   - Category-based grouping
   - Priority-based grouping
3. Set quiet hours
   - Respect time zones
   - Consider team schedules
   - Allow overrides for emergencies

### Team Communication
1. Standardize notification settings
   - Team-wide configurations
   - Shared filtering rules
   - Common priority definitions
2. Document notification protocols
   - Clear guidelines
   - Regular updates
   - Accessible documentation
3. Regular review of notification effectiveness
   - Monthly assessments
   - Team feedback
   - Continuous improvement

## Markup Conventions

### Basic Frame
```markdown
â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢
[Content]
â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢â—¤â—¢
```

### Follow-up Markers
- ğŸ“‹ **Checklist**
  - For listing items to be verified
  - Used in task summaries
- â“ **User Confirmation Required**
  - For items needing user input
  - Used in questions and decisions
- âš ï¸ **Warning**
  - For important notices
  - Used for critical information
- âœ… **Recommended**
  - For suggested settings
  - Used in best practices
- â— **Action Required**
  - For immediate actions
  - Used for urgent requests

### Status Indicators
- âœ… Completed
- â³ In Progress
- âŒ Not Started
- âš ï¸ Needs Attention

### Section Formatting
```markdown
ã€Section Nameã€‘
1. Primary Item
   - Sub-item
   - Sub-item
```

### Priority Levels
- ğŸ”´ High Priority
- ğŸŸ¡ Medium Priority
- ğŸŸ¢ Low Priority

### Follow-up Template
```markdown
ã€Follow-up Requestã€‘
â“ **Confirmation Items**
[Specific Questions]

âœ… **Options**
1. [Option 1]
2. [Option 2]

â³ **Response Deadline**
[Deadline]

â— **Importance Level**
[Priority Level]
```

### Error and Warning Format
```markdown
âš ï¸ **Warning**
[Warning Content]

âŒ **Error**
[Error Details]

â„¹ï¸ **Information**
[Additional Info]
